sql:
SELECT state_name, gdp_nominal_per_capita
FROM member_states
ORDER BY gdp_nominal_per_capita DESC;

SELECT state_name, population
FROM member_states
ORDER BY population DESC;

SELECT state_name
FROM member_states
WHERE population = (SELECT MIN(population) FROM member_states);

SELECT state_name
FROM member_states
WHERE gdp_nominal_per_capita > (SELECT AVG(gdp_nominal_per_capita) FROM member_states);

external_knowledge:
- "blossomed with over a decade of nurturing" refers to states having more than 10 years of population data; 
- "average growth rates" refers to the calculated average population growth rates; 
- "lingering shadow of their realm status" refers to the presence or absence of any realm status recorded for these states; 
- "unique explorers who journeyed to their gates in the year of the phoenix (2020)" refers to the count of distinct user IDs who accessed the state's information in the year 2020.

